de.learnlib.parallelism

Class StaticParallelOracle<I,O>

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.learnlib.parallelism.StaticParallelOracle<I,O>
  • Type Parameters:
    I - input symbol class
    O - output class
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    MembershipOracle<I,O>, ParallelOracle<I,O>

    @ParametersAreNonnullByDefault
public class StaticParallelOracle<I,O>
extends Object
implements ParallelOracle<I,O>
    A membership oracle that statically distributes a set of queries among several threads.

    An incoming set of queries is divided into a given number of batches, such that the sizes of all batches differ by at most one. This keeps the required synchronization effort low, but if some batches are "harder" (for whatever reason) than others, the load can be very unbalanced.

    Author:
    Malte Isberner
